Stock Solutions

IPTG Isopropyl thiogalactoside, or isopropyl beta-D-thiogalactopyranoside
0.1 M solution – 0.238 g in 10 ml of water
filter sterilize
store -20ºC
X-gal 5-bromo-4-chloro-3-indolyl-beta-D-galactopyranoside.
20 mg/ml solution in DMSO (dimethyl sulfoxide)
light sensitive
filter sterilize
store -20ºC
 

Using IPTG and X-gal for blue/white selection on Petri plates

Method 1: spiking on pre-made plates

Spread 40 ul of IPTG and 40 ul of X-gal on top of the plate with a hockey stick spreader or sterile glass beads
dry thoroughly before use
Method 2: Incorporating IPTG and X-gal into the plates before pouring

Mix agar and media as usual, cool as you would for antibiotic addition
add IPTG to a final concentration of 0.1 mM IPTG (1 ul IPTG stock solution per ml of media)
add X-gal to a final concentration of 40 ug/ml (2 ul of X-gal stock solution per ml of media)
add selection antibiotics as usual
